<span id="freeTextContainer1125252273747958955">I did not realize that I was listening to an abridged audio version of this novel until after 3 hours of listening when it came to an abrupt end. &quot;Abridged&quot; was not written anywhere when I looked it up at my library nor on the copy I borrowed. I&apos;m not even sure I should count it as having &quot;read&quot; it. Also, the narrator was a surprisingly poor choice. He sounded like he was having an asthma attack while reading so I heard every heavy intake of his breathe for 3 hours.<br/><br/>I am giving this novel 2 stars</span>
  <span id="freeText1125252273747958955" style="display:none">I did not realize that I was listening to an abridged audio version of this novel until after 3 hours of listening when it came to an abrupt end. "Abridged" was not written anywhere when I looked it up at my library nor on the copy I borrowed. I'm not even sure I should count it as having "read" it. Also, the narrator was a surprisingly poor choice. He sounded like he was having an asthma attack while reading so I heard every heavy intake of his breathe for 3 hours.<br /><br />I am giving this novel 2 stars. I cannot write a review because I must have missed most of the story, and from what I've heard from my informed friends, all of the sex scenes. What a waste of time.</span>
